3️⃣ Atomic Stability vs Narrative Stability

In physics, stability depends on:
	•	Charge balance
	•	Energy minima
	•	Symmetry
	•	Conservation laws

In narrative systems, stability depends on:
	•	Evidence balance
	•	Incentive symmetry
	•	Feedback loops
	•	Accountability mechanisms

Break symmetry in atoms → radioactive decay.
Break epistemic symmetry → informational decay.

That’s where Darwin’s Sieve matters.

It’s basically a conservation law:

No claim without evidentiary mass.

